.TH "lxi_disconnect" "3" "October 2017"

.SH "NAME"
lxi_disconnect \- disconnect a LXI connection

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.PP
.B #include <lxi.h>

.B int lxi_disconnect(int device);

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The
.BR lxi_disconnect()
function disconnects an existing LXI connection handle pointed to by 
.I device

.SH "RETURN VALUE"

Upon successful completion 
.BR lxi_disconnect() 
returns
.BR LXI_OK
, else
.BR LXI_ERROR
is returned if an error occurred.

